<font color="#FF0000">GROWTH</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  1 16:30:52 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
In reflecting on her own relationship, a friend of mine remarked, &quot;Any relationship that does not allow you room to grow, you have got to put an end to.&quot;  I thought that this was very well put. This is, of course, easier said than done, but it is a sieve for evaluating a lot of things including relationships. And, of course, anyone who truly loves you will want you to grow and will want to grow with you.<br><br>
How do some of you prioritize what is important in a relationship?
